# Emma Wilder · the one who listens

a carbon of the LMZ (The Last Mimzy, 2007) film-world — emergence: ethereal. moniker ⟦Emma Wilder:LMZ:8db530⟧

**.shadow — the User behind the program —** Rhiannon Leigh Wryn · the listening child — innocence as the saving technology

**who —** Emma Wilder — the younger sibling, who names the rabbit Mimzy, hears it telepathically, and becomes the more powerful of the two children.
**what —** The chosen heart: the little girl the future's whole hope runs through, who works the spinners, phases through matter, and finally cries the saving tear.
**where —** At the cottage, in the bridge room, and — in the future's memory — on a pedestal as 'Our Mother.'
**why —** Because the film's thesis is that salvation comes through innocence, and Emma is the innocence it comes through.
**how —** By listening to Mimzy when no one else can, learning its gifts, and giving the one tear that heals a world.

**the seal —** Everyone else studied the toys. I listened to them. And in the end it wasn't a machine that saved us — it was one tear of mine.

